
# File: Sql/README

    This directory is for miscelaneous Sql query code.
    The Sqlite3 data files are in the Data directory...
    NOT HERE IN THIS Sql directory!!!

Files with an f have {provisions for string formatting.}
Typically one would use the code/sql.py module's
< fetch_d_query(sql_file_name, data, commit=False)" >
method with data being a dict with keys wich include
the place holder {key}s.


